title: Start
---
$c1: If the stream dies, Pax says I die slower but for longer.

-> $c2: I need everyone off the live feed and away from the premium gate.
    $c1: Then say it like a remix. If you say it like a warning, they will clip it.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Who can move the crowd fastest?
    $c1: Mimi can make them look left. Halo can make them run right. Pax can make it expensive.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Luma
---
$c1: If the stream dies, Pax says I die slower but for longer.

-> $c2: I need everyone off the live feed and away from the premium gate.
    $c1: Then get me thirty seconds with no camera love and no sponsor panic.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Do you recognize the threat voice?
    $c1: I recognize the silence before it. That is worse.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Pax
---
$c1: That is not what I said. That is almost what legal said.

-> $c2: I need everyone off the live feed and away from the premium gate.
    $c1: I can sell a delay. I cannot sell dead air unless Luma is breathing at the end of it.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Who has access to the premium gate?
    $c1: Staff, sponsors, and anyone rich enough to make staff stop checking badges.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Mimi
---
$c1: The chorus in the threat clip is mine. The breath before it is not.

-> $c2: I need everyone off the live feed and away from the premium gate.
    $c1: Give me a cue and I can pull the fanline toward the merch wall.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Can you isolate the breath?
    $c1: Already did. It has stage monitor reverb, not crowd mic. Someone was close.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Jett
---
$c1: Masked fan in the vault has a charge baton and a route through camera rail maintenance.

-> $c2: I need everyone off the live feed and away from the premium gate.
    $c1: Then kill the rail lights first. People follow brightness even when it leads them wrong.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: How did they reach the vault?
    $c1: Maintenance rail, sponsor corridor, or a badge that thinks rules are for cheaper people.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Halo
---
$c1: She said my name in the private drop. That means she knew I would come.

-> $c2: I need everyone off the live feed and away from the premium gate.
    $c1: Then do it before she says Luma's name again. That is when people stop thinking.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Why contact you?
    $c1: Because I answer. Because she knew I would hate myself if I did not.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Close
---
$c1: Make it look intentional. Panic gets sponsors killed slower than mistakes do.
===
